# Engineering

Application or library source code for {{PROJECT_NAME}}.

## Layout
- `src/` - production source
- `tests/` - unit and integration tests
- Build/package config at room root (`package.json`, `pyproject.toml`, `*.csproj`, etc.)

## Rules
- Language: {{ENGINEERING_LANGUAGE}}, idiomatic style.
- Tests run from a single command. CI runs the same command.
- Dependencies pinned. Lockfile checked in.
- No secrets in source. Config via env vars or a secret store.
- Public surface area documented; internal helpers don't need it.
- Build is reproducible. Errors fail fast at boundaries with actionable messages.
- One-off scripts go in `reference/` or `automation/`, not here.

